reviews.title: Great sushi, best we had.
reviews.text:
We visit Suki Yaki often since it's close by and we are never disappointed. Ok, it could be a bit more cosy and sometimes service is a tad slow, but the sushi is simply devine as are the other options one can choose. Its AYCE and well worth every euro!
And if you have young kids, there is a seperate playroom where they can amuse themselves while you enjoy your dinner!

articleContent.title: Your Ultimate Melbourne Summer with AO Travel & Experiences Packages

seoInfo.metaDescription: It’s game, set, and a winning Melbourne adventure for tennis fans heading to the Australian Open in January. With AO Travel & Experiences - the official travel provider of the AO - you’ll make the most of every break in play, stepping beyond the court to discover everything the vibrant city of Melbourne has to offer.

Athens is one of those cities I always thought I could do in a day or two, hitting the Acropolis and grabbing a gyro before moving on. But the more time I’ve spent here, the more I’ve realized just how much this city has to offer—and how rewarding it is to slow down and dig deeper. I love the cool neighborhoods full of open-air wine bars and shops run by local designers that put a new spin on Greek style. And then there’s the city’s exciting art scene, ranging from edgy street murals in Exarchia to sleek galleries in Kolonaki.
